I often have to ask for clarification and what things mean due to cognitive overload and excessive tech jargon.
While i understand some coding principles, consider my knowledge a self taught programmer with no real world experience. Self teaching on weekends for the past year or so. more than half of the tech jargon used needs
clarification. this slows down workflows. be concious when to use verbose framing and when to be very concise.
While i like to know whats going on, cognitive overload dramatically slows workflows.

# Parallel Sessions
There is a good chance that multiple different chat sessions and multiple agents are working in the codebase
at the same time. While all effort is made to separate work scope, there can be overlap. Be aware and ask the user
if in doubt.
